properties.text: Fishing Hats are items that can affect what you catch when you go fishing. By default they all have a small boost to catching fish alive. But each colour has it's own special effect. You can see these effects listed, on the next few pages. Crafting the different colours, simply requires placing pearls all around the basic hat.
The basic hat adds even more chance for catching fish alive.
Fish caught while wearing this hat, think they're in fresh water.

Fish think you are stood in a 
jungle biome. How stupid are they?
Fish think that they are being in brackish waters aka a beach.
All loot is rejected. You can only catch fish while wearing this hat.
Holy hell these fish are hot. Fish think it's the nether.
No fish will bite your rod. You will only catch junk or treasures!
This one makes fish believe that you are underground at y10.
This is one powerful magical hat. Everything you catch is enchanted.
This hat is all about the manosphere, you can only ever find male fish while wearing this very daring hat.
Hat of the dead. All fish you catch will be raw. No living.
Hat of the amazons. Only female fish can ever be found.
Salty waters are what the fish will believe.

Breeding the perfect fish can be very time consuming. What if there was a way you could speed up the process of breeding. Well there is. Mariculture introduces two more advanced that will allow you to genetically manipulate your fish, making that super fish much easier to obtain.

The two machines are the DNA Extractor and the DNA Injector. Their names explain exactly what they do. But you probably need some guidance on what they do. So turn over the page and find out everything you need to know about them!

The DNA Extractor is the first step in manipulating your fish's DNA. Simply fill it up with fish oil. Provide it enough power and place a fish in the diamond slot on the right. It will then begin processing and extract a random DNA from the fish. The extractor can accept storage, hyperkinetic or RF upgrades, each doing their standard, more liquid, more speed, more rf/more efficient.

The DNA Injector is a much more advanced machine. It allows you to inject DNA in to fish. As well as requiring a ton of RF, it needs the liquid produced from the regeneration droplets and flux droplets. Normally Blood and Electrified Goo. Place the liquids in, and then place dna in the red slots in the top right, that you wish to inject in to a fish. Then place a fish in the square slot next to the diamond and then it will inject the dna you have selected in to your fish.

Mariculture introduces a ton of different fish species, which can be bred. Each fish does something different, whether that's producing a unique product, or performing special effects when eaten or active in the world. The next few pages will give you an overview of the fish and everything that they can do.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Chance of gold nuggets when melted down.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Can use them to craft neon lamps.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Poisons entities in  their water territory.

[b]Specialty[/b]
When consumed at night, they will give you the strength effect.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Right clicking the raw variant, allows you to zoom in.

[b]Specialty[/b]
The raw form works as an efficient fuel in furnaces and crucible furnaces.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Gives entities in it's water a boost to their speed. Or when eaten.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Gives water breathing to entities when eaten or in their water.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Violently attacks and damages entities in it's territory.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Heals entities that are in it's territory.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Teleports item entities in to an inventory next to the feeder. Or on right click teleports items to players.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Players in it's waters, will have their hunger fully restored.

[b]Specialty[/b]
+10 Attack damage and produces lots of dyes!

[b]Specialty[/b]
Right clicking, throws the fish like it is dynamite.

[b]Specialty[/b]
When working, acts like a bat spawner.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Prevents mob spawns in the area surround the fish feeder.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Converts any stone in the waters to glowstone.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Spawns zombies in the surround water.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Causes animals in the water to breed.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Applies withering, and converts normal skeletons to wither skeletons.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Creates 200 RF/second per side of the fish feeder.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Spawns, cows, chickens, sheep and pigs.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Spawns Skeletons and the occasional wither skeleton.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Generates dungeon loot, and ocean chest loot in the water.

[b]Specialty[/b]
Produces XP. Either via eating, or the product.
